  "notes": [
    "The Biophysics major is designed to provide students with a flexible scientific/technical training that allows them to explore different career paths and tailor their class work to their scientific interests. The program aims at providing an opportunity to the students to become scientific leaders, bringing the analytic and experimental techniques of different fields to bear on the fascinating world of the physics of living systems. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for admission to this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One and a half years of Calculus through Multivariable, One course in Linear Algebra, One course in Differential Equations, One year of Calculus Based Physics (Mechanics, Electricity, and Magnetism), One year of General Chemistry, and One course in Biology with Lab for the major (Cellular, Molecular) It is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED that the remainder of the major prep be completed prior to transfer. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// www.pa.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed."
